cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 250 mi WSW of Grand Cayman
cyclone.trajectory: Moving ENE-NE toward the Cayman Islands and central Cuba today, forecast to cross the Florida Keys/South Florida Sunday night then enter the southeastern Gulf of Mexico and drift northwest toward the northeast Gulf by mid-week.

weather_observation.watch_coast: Sebastian Inlet FL southward around the Florida peninsula to Bonita Beach, the Florida Keys, Florida Bay, and Lake Okeechobee
weather_observation.warning_coast: Northwestern Bahamas and portions of central Cuba; Cayman Islands
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Central Cuba, Cayman Islands, Northwestern Bahamas, South & Central Florida peninsula, Florida Keys, northeast Gulf Coast
weather_observation.wind: Breezy conditions possible mid-week; probability of sustained tropical-storm-force winds at the port remains below 5%.
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected along the Georgia coast from Eta.
weather_observation.rainfall: Periods of rain Tuesday–Wednesday could produce 1–3 inches, locally higher, but widespread 4-inch totals are not anticipated.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Minor coastal rip current risk possible mid-week due to distant swells.
